cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about language models and grammatical dependencies. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of different models and their learning capabilities. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with neural language models and their ability to learn human-like generalizations. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of neural networks in language modeling. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses experimental methods from psycholinguistics to compare the performance of different models.
